Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2009 15:08:47 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 10/15] p2020ds: Change NOR Flash partition to align with u-boot

Since in u-boot the default NOR Flash partition is:

uImage_amp_core0	0xE8000000
uImage_amp_core1	0xE8800000
ramdisk			0xE9000000
edink			0xEBE00000
uImage_smp		0xEE000000
p2020ds_smp.dtb		0xEE800000
p2020ds_amp_core0.dtb	0xEE900000
p2020ds_amp_core1.dtb	0xEEa00000
u-boot			0xEFF80000

So change NOR Flash partition in dts to align with
the default partition in u-boot.

Signed-off-by: Yang Shi <yang.shi@windirver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts |   12 ++++++------
 1 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts
index 375b5a8..be1097d 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts
+++ b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/p2020ds.dts
@@ -87,17 +87,17 @@
                                read-only;
                        };
 
-                       kernel@4000000 {
-                               reg = <0x04000000 0x00400000>;
+                       jffs2@4000000 {
+                               reg = <0x04000000 0x02000000>;
                                read-only;
                        };
 
-                       jffs2@4400000 {
-                               reg = <0x04400000 0x03b00000>;
+                       kernel@6000000 {
+                               reg = <0x06000000 0x00800000>;
                        };
 
-                       dtb@7f00000 {
-                               reg = <0x07f00000 0x00080000>;
+                       dtb@6800000 {
+                               reg = <0x06800000 0x01780000>;
                                read-only;
                        };
 
